Of the history of the book nothing fur- ther is known, till, in the year 1817, it was purchased by Mr. Surtees from a bookseller in Leicester‚ and upon its arrival at Mainsforth, was taken to Auckland, and presented to the Bishop of Durham, who then and there marked it with his name, “ S. With respect to the Volume itself a few words may suffice. It is of the solio size, upon strong paper, and consists of 166 solie, or 332 pages, written in an elegant hand, which frequently imitates the printing type of the period.
